{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 43,
  "title": "第四十三章（至柔）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "天下之至柔，馳騁於天下之致堅。无有入於无間，吾是以知无為之有益。不言之教，无為之益。天下希能及之矣。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "至柔者，水也。至堅者，金石也。水能貫堅入剛，無所不通。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無有謂道也。道無形質，故能出入無間，通神明濟群生也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 22,
          "end": 23
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "吾見道無為而萬物自化成，是以知無為之有益於人也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 32,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "法道不言，師之以身。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 37,
          "end": 38
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "法道無為，治身則有益於精神，治國則有益於萬民，不勞煩也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 50,
          "end": 50
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天下，人主也。希能有及道無為之治身治國也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "氣無所不入，水無所不出於經。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "虛無柔弱，無所不通，無有不可窮，至柔不可折，以此推之，故知無為之有益也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 50,
          "end": 50
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
